views.text: In the event that two (or more) teams finish with an equal number of points, the following rules break the tie: 1. Head-to-head games between the teams concerned 1a. Points total 1b. Goal difference 1c. Goals scored 2. Goal difference 3. Goals scored 4. Disciplinary Points 5. European Qualifiers Ranking  If two teams are tied on points, goals scored, and goals conceded, and they play their final group match against each other, a penalty shootout will determine their rankings, provided no other teams in the group have the same points.
To be featured on the list, players must meet the criteria of playing at least 60% of the total minutes in the competition.
Top Stats show you remarkable stats that certain players achieved in a league match.
